;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
;Front lawn
NUMBER 1201
 NAME Herlighy Home
 REGION 0
 OUTDOOR_FLOOR
 CHANNEL 1
 FIXED_LIGHT

 EXIT N 1202

;      tree,    Dead      Oak
ITEM 0 1062 ADJ1=261 ADJ2=646
;      door
ITEM 1 351 VAL2=0 LOCKED

*DESCRIPTION_START
The yard's dead grass and gnarled oak trees are dwarfed by the dark,
hulking mass of the long abandoned Herlighy home. The door, warped and
losing its paint, is boarded shut, as are the windows. The yard extends
north along the right side of the house.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
You notice the initials T+M carved into the gray bark of the old tree.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB OPEN 1
 ECHO PLAYER The door is boarded shut and can't be opened.
 CLEARVERB
ENDIF

;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
;Right side
NUMBER 1202
 NAME Herlighy Home
 REGION 0
 OUTDOOR_FLOOR
 FIXED_LIGHT
 CHANNEL 1

*DESCRIPTION_START
Chilling mist creates a deep gloom, filling this side of the house like a dark
pudding. Anything could be lurking in the deep shadows created by the mist
and shrubbery. A broken cellar window suggests a means of entry, but the
blackness beyond yields no clue as to whether you could get back out.
*DESCRIPTION_END

 EXIT S 1201

 ;    Window,     broken
 ITEM 0 1123 ADJ1=113

 IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You climb through the window... hang by your fingers... and drop into the blackness.
  ECHO OTHERS %N climbs through a broken window... and drops into the darkness.
  DISBAND
  MOVE 1203
  AFFECT 1203
  ECHO OTHERS %N drops from the window above you.
 ENDIF


;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
;Cellar
NUMBER 1203
 NAME Herlighy Home
 REGION 0
 INDOOR_FLOOR
 FIXED_LIGHT
 CHANNEL 1

*DESCRIPTION_START
A damp chill pours out of the broken cellar window high above you. In
the darkness you can barely make out some rickety stairs leading up to the
cellar door. Other items loom about, but in the dim light you can't
identify them.
*DESCRIPTION_END

 ;    Window,     broken
 ITEM 0 1123 ADJ1=113
 ; Stairway, rickety
 ITEM 1 962 ADJ1=784 VAL2=1204 UNLOCKED

 IFPREVERB HIDE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You grope around, trying to hide.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gropes around, trying to hide.
 ENDIF

 IFENTRY
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 2
 ENDIF


