;Foyer
NUMBER 1208
 NAME Herlighy Home
 REGION 0
 INDOOR_FLOOR
 FIXED_LIGHT
 CHANNEL 1

*DESCRIPTION_START
Standing in the foyer you observe what in its heyday was a majestic manse and 
is now a dilapidated wreck. To the west is a dark kitchen and to your right
a closet door under the stairway leading to the second floor. An arch leads
into a dim dining room.
*DESCRIPTION_END

 ; Kitchen
 EXIT W 1206
 ;   Stairs,   wooden
 ITEM 0 962 ADJ1=1101 VAL2=1209
 ; Stairwell closet door
 ITEM 1 352 VAL2=1219 UNLOCKED
 ; Bannister,   wooden
 ITEM 2 1403 ADJ1=1101
 ; Arch
 ITEM 3 17 VAL2=1207
 ; Door
 ITEM 4 352 VAL2=0 LOCKED

 IFPREVERB OPEN 4
  ECHO PLAYER The door is boarded shut and can't be opened.
  CLEARVERB
 ENDIF

 IFVERB RECALL -1
  ECHO PLAYER For hide and seek, both start in the foyer. When the Seeker goes into the stairwell closet, the Hider has 5 seconds to get away before the Seeker can move again. When the Seeker sees the Hider, the Seeker wins.
 ENDIF

 IFVERB GO 0
  RANDOM ITEMVAL5 1 100 0
  IFVAR ITEMVAL5 > 50
   ECHO PLAYER You hear a creak as you climb the stairs.
   STRCPY 0 "There's_a_creak_as_someone_climbs_the_stairs
   ; 1204 Laundry room
   AFFECT 1204
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1205 Mop closet
   AFFECT 1205
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1206 Kitchen
   AFFECT 1206
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1207 Dining room
   AFFECT 1207
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1208 Foyer
   AFFECT 1208
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1209 Hallway, south end
   AFFECT 1209
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1210 Hallway, north end
   AFFECT 1210
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1211 Hall closet
   AFFECT 1211
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1212 Study
   AFFECT 1212
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1213 Bedroom, south
   AFFECT 1213
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1214 Bedroom, north
   AFFECT 1214
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1215 Bathroom
   AFFECT 1215
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1216 Bedroom closet, south
   AFFECT 1216
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1217 Bedroom closet, north
   AFFECT 1217
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1218 Attic
   AFFECT 1218
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; 1219 Coat closet
   AFFECT 1219

   EQUAL ROUNDTIME 2
  ENDIF
 ENDIF

 IFPREVERB HIDE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You grope around, trying to hide.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gropes around, trying to hide.
 ENDIF

 IFENTRY
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 1
 ENDIF


;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
;South end of hallway
NUMBER 1209
 NAME Herlighy Home
 REGION 0
 INDOOR_FLOOR
 FIXED_LIGHT
 CHANNEL 1

*DESCRIPTION_START
A tattered runner extends from this end of the narrow hallway to the other.
Across from the two doors here is a stairway leading down, adorned by a
wooden bannister. 
*DESCRIPTION_END

 EXIT N 1210

 ; Stairway
 ITEM 0 962 VAL2=1208
 ; Bedroom Door, wooden
 ITEM 1 352 ADJ1=1101 VAL2=1213 UNLOCKED
 ; Bathroom Door, stained
 ITEM 2 352 ADJ1=936 VAL2=1215 UNLOCKED
 ; Bannister
 ITEM 3 1403 ADJ1=1101

 ; ITEMVAL3 is destination here
 EQUAL ITEMVAL3 0
 
 ; ITEMVAL4 is flag for use of bannister here
 EQUAL ITEMVAL4 0

 IFPREVERB GO 3
  CLEARVERB
  EQUAL ITEMVAL4 1
  EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1208
 ENDIF
 
 IFVAR ITEMVAL4 = 1
  ECHO PLAYER You hop up, planting your bottom on the bannister and swiftly slide to the lower floor, neatly polishing the bannister in the process.
  ECHO OTHERS %N hops onto the bannister and swiftly slides to the bottom, leaving it clean behind %i.
  DISBAND
  APPEAR %N has a dirty bottom.
  MOVE 1208
  AFFECT 1208
  ECHO OTHERS %N comes sliding down the now-clean bannister and lands next to you.
  ; ITEMVAL3 holds destination
  EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1208
 ENDIF

 ; ITEMVAL5 is door condition now
 IFVERB OPEN 2
  EQUAL ITEMVAL5 0
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 1
 ENDIF

 IFVERB CLOSE 2
  ; If it was open
  IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0
   ECHO PLAYER There's a 'thunk' as it closes.
   STRCPY 0 "You_hear_a_door_close
   ; Foyer
   AFFECT 1208
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; North bedroom
   AFFECT 1208
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
   ; South bedroom
   AFFECT 1213
   ECHO OTHERS %0.
  ENDIF
  EQUAL ITEMVAL5 1
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 1
 ENDIF

 IFPREVERB HIDE -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You grope around, trying to hide.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gropes around, trying to hide.
 ENDIF

 IFENTRY
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 1
  ; Downstairs closet telltale
  AFFECT 1219
  ECHO OTHERS You hear a footstep overhead.
  ; Bathroom telltale
  AFFECT 1215
  ECHO OTHERS You hear a footstep outside the door.
  ; Bedroom telltale
  AFFECT 1213
  ECHO OTHERS You hear a footstep outside the door.
 ENDIF

 ; Went in bedroom
 IFVERB GO 1
  EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1213
 ENDIF

 ; Went in bathroom
 IFVERB GO 2
  EQUAL ITEMVAL3 1215
 ENDIF

 ; Went north
 IFPREVERB N -1
   ; tell the bathroom
   AFFECT 1215
   ECHO OTHERS You sense someone move away from the door.
   ; tell the bathroom
   AFFECT 1213
   ECHO OTHERS You sense someone move away from the door.
 ENDIF

 IFVAR ITEMVAL3 > 0
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! 1215
   ; tell the bathroom
   AFFECT 1215
   ECHO OTHERS You sense someone move away from the door.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL3 ! 1213
   ; tell the bathroom
   AFFECT 1213
   ECHO OTHERS You sense someone move away from the door.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF

